LoS 1 is a third person action something in between the God of War, Devil May Cry and Darksiders (1) sequence of the levels, where you can return to the previous levels to check some secrets using your newly obtained powers.
The levels most of the time are straight line corridors, sometimes with puzzles, (most of them are easy, some require try and error approach and 1 extremely difficult), with good exceptions like cave labyrinth and vampire castle gardens.
Good:
+ Visual design - stunning distinct locations, fighting arenas;
+ Music - the game sounds like the epic adventure it is, very suitable for fighting 100 meter golems, hordes  of lycans and vampires;
+ Bosses - LoS series excels at interesting and distinctive bosses that have unique features for most of them
+ Fighting mechanics - enemies rarely attack from the blind spots, with good positioning you always have a change to dodge or block the attack; high level difficulty requires to combine subweapons like silver daggers, holy water bombs and so on to counter some enemies; moving around battle arenas feels good and Gabriel reacts to the input very fast and feels nimble; 

Bad:
- Enemies - they seem to be generic and 1 type reuses just 1 model, that could be ok, if the game had more enemy types;
- Platforming - LoS 2 improved that part of the game drastically, but first  game has too many sections that frustrate the player because of how inconsistent Gabriel grabs the ledges;
- Simple gamedesign of many locations;
- Story - its cheesy, generic and mediocre, especially one distinct cutscene makes me put the story to the drawbacks, but it gives a  motivation to the hero to move on, and have bits of interesting lore;
- Static camera - some secrets utilise weird camera angles and sometimes they are just not optimal. leaving some blind spots (which requires positioning to mitigate).

Overall its a good game, but decision to buy it or not I would put on how much did you liked the second game, because it is really awesome.
I have no clue how LoS has more points on metacritic than LoS 2, its freaking Jaqcue Fresco riddle to me

